1
00:00:05,797 --> 00:00:09,635
<i>["Day You Laugh"</i>
<i>by Toyonaga Toshiyuki]</i>

2
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:16,642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

3
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:25,275
[man singing in Japanese]

4
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:32,282
<i>♪ ♪</i>

5
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:53,971
‐ I don't know why you did it,

6
00:00:53,971 --> 00:00:55,847
but you dragged Anri into this.

7
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:57,557
You will accept my anger.

8
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:59,726
IZAYA: You see?
Whatever problems they had,

9
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:02,854
they're just a big old stain
on the pavement now.

10
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:04,147
‐ Forgive the intrusion.

11
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:05,357
‐ You see, I need you to locate

12
00:01:05,357 --> 00:01:06,692
a particular young lady

13
00:01:06,692 --> 00:01:07,859
and kidnap her.

14
00:01:07,859 --> 00:01:10,070
IZAYA:
Damn. I underestimated them.

15
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:11,989
‐ The Black Rider!
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

16
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:18,996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17
00:02:00,579 --> 00:02:04,416
RIO: All day,
he'd been lying there waiting.

18
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:08,295
Waiting for someone
to come and kill him.

19
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:12,883
IZAYA:
Maybe it'll be Shizu‐chan.

20
00:02:12,883 --> 00:02:15,427
Or maybe her.

21
00:02:15,427 --> 00:02:18,472
Or maybe...

22
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:21,433
He does have
one hell of a grudge against me.

23
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:23,769
If the news
about my getting stabbed

24
00:02:23,769 --> 00:02:25,729
broke this morning,

25
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:27,773
someone special should come

26
00:02:27,773 --> 00:02:30,942
any second now
to finish the job.

27
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:32,778
<i>[eerie instrumental music]</i>

28
00:02:32,778 --> 00:02:35,072
[clock ticking]

29
00:02:35,072 --> 00:02:42,079
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:47,125
[footsteps clomping]

31
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:50,754
I've been waiting patiently
all day.

32
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:53,256
It'd be a shame
if I didn't get to end it

33
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:55,050
with a...bang.

34
00:02:56,218 --> 00:02:59,304
Come in, whoever you are.

35
00:03:00,389 --> 00:03:04,476
RIO: He loved people.
A lot.

36
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:05,977
NURSE: Hello, Mr. Orihara.

37
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:07,688
How are we doing?

38
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:10,065
Let's get a fresh IV in you.

39
00:03:11,525 --> 00:03:13,276
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:15,320
IZAYA: All right.

41
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:18,198
I'm in the hospital.

42
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:20,826
JINNAI: Besides,
you're looking kind of stressed.

43
00:03:20,826 --> 00:03:23,829
I think a nap
would do you a world of good.

44
00:03:31,503 --> 00:03:35,090
[Izaya grimacing]

45
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:41,805
[crowd murmuring]

46
00:03:41,805 --> 00:03:44,266
JINNAI: Oh, and since you asked,

47
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:47,352
my name is Jinnai Yodogiri,

48
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:50,397
and I'm pleased
to make your acquaintance.

49
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:54,651
NURSE: I'm sure dealing
with the police this morning

50
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:56,403
was stressful.

51
00:03:56,403 --> 00:03:57,696
‐ [chuckles]
It was.

52
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:59,364
Not used to being interrogated
like that.

53
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:01,992
‐ Good.
I'd be concerned if you were.

54
00:04:01,992 --> 00:04:04,161
MAN: You think
the stabbing was random?

55
00:04:04,161 --> 00:04:06,538
IZAYA: I don't know
who'd want to attack me.

56
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:07,789
Honest.

57
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:10,083
Please, officer,
don't worry about me.

58
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,210
Just catch
the maniac who did this.

59
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:15,088
The people of this city
would breathe easier.

60
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:16,506
BOTH: Hmm.

61
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:18,049
IZAYA:
Judging by their reactions,

62
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:21,803
I bet they found
the knife in my stash pocket.

63
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,889
Guess I'll sneak out tonight,

64
00:04:23,889 --> 00:04:26,308
even though
I'm still feeling ouch‐y.

65
00:04:26,308 --> 00:04:27,934
NURSE:
Your color's looking good.

66
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:30,228
At the rate you're healing,
you should be discharged

67
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:31,521
in no time at all.

68
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,565
‐ Now,
that would be disappointing.

69
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:35,233
It's so comfortable here.

70
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:37,068
I was hoping I could stay
a little bit longer‐‐

71
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:39,780
RIO: His love for people
was an obsession.

72
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:43,492
That's why he watched
their lives so closely.

73
00:04:43,492 --> 00:04:44,493
A whole lot of lives.

74
00:04:44,493 --> 00:04:45,535
‐ Speaking of pain,

75
00:04:45,535 --> 00:04:47,037
you wouldn't happen to know

76
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:49,456
if my stabbing made the news
this morning, would you?

77
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:50,957
NURSE:
Actually, they talked about it

78
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:53,293
on TV King's
"Bokusatsu! Morning Star" show.

79
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,628
They even mentioned your name‐‐

80
00:04:54,628 --> 00:04:56,421
RIO: He liked
watching from the shadows.

81
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:57,422
‐ Oh, did they, now?

82
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:58,465
<i>[dramatic music plays]</i>

83
00:04:58,465 --> 00:04:59,966
WOMAN: Here's our next story.

84
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,259
Around 9:00 last night,

85
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:03,553
in a shopping arcade
near Sendai Station,

86
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:06,765
a man was critically stabbed
by an unknown assailant.

87
00:05:06,765 --> 00:05:10,060
The victim has been identified
as Izaya Orihara.

88
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:12,062
‐ Why are you bringing
so much stuff?

89
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:13,522
It's just a day trip.

90
00:05:13,522 --> 00:05:16,107
SHINRA: You know what they say‐‐
better safe than sorry.

91
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:18,068
‐ Why do humans make
such a big deal

92
00:05:18,068 --> 00:05:20,111
about going somewhere
on their day off?

93
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:22,614
You just end up
exhausting yourselves.

94
00:05:22,614 --> 00:05:24,491
‐ Oh, we don't do it to relax.

95
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:26,785
We do it
to shake things up in our lives.

96
00:05:26,785 --> 00:05:28,745
Going on weird little adventures

97
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:31,289
breaks up
the monotony of our day‐to‐day.

98
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:33,625
It recharges the soul.

99
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:34,960
Oh, almost forgot.

100
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:37,963
My favorite boxers!
Ha‐ha!

101
00:05:37,963 --> 00:05:39,548
Can't leave home without 'em.

102
00:05:39,548 --> 00:05:43,468
CELTY: Seriously?
SHINRA: Duh. Of course not.

103
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,220
‐ Where are we going
that you need to bring

104
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:48,807
an extra pair of boxers?

105
00:05:48,807 --> 00:05:51,226
MAN: Is it
the city of Higashimurayama?

106
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:54,062
After a recent searching of‐‐

107
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:57,524
‐ Time to hit the road
for adventure!

108
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:59,150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

109
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:00,986
MAN: Dude,
I know who your little bro is.

110
00:06:00,986 --> 00:06:02,737
He's famous <i>and</i> loaded.

111
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:04,656
I wonder how he'd feel
if I went and told the world

112
00:06:04,656 --> 00:06:07,284
you were the muscle
for a loan shark.

113
00:06:07,284 --> 00:06:08,493
Now, we don't want that,

114
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,036
so how about
you forget what I owe,

115
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,037
I keep my mouth shut,

116
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:12,455
and we call it square.

117
00:06:12,455 --> 00:06:13,999
Sound good?

118
00:06:13,999 --> 00:06:16,459
[blow resounds]
Whoa‐ho‐ho‐ho‐ho!

119
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:18,003
WOMAN:
The victim has been identified

120
00:06:18,003 --> 00:06:19,421
as Izaya Orihara.

121
00:06:19,421 --> 00:06:22,465
A large crowd had formed
by the time police arrived.

122
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:24,259
Several witnesses told us...
[doorbell rings]

123
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:26,678
That Mr. Orihara collapsed
in a heap in the street.

124
00:06:26,678 --> 00:06:28,680
AKANE: Uncle Akabayashi!

125
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,931
[Akabayashi chuckles]

126
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:31,433
AKABAYASHI:
When'd you get so tall?

127
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:34,060
‐ No way is this normal.

128
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:37,272
What the hell does a girl
her age want to talk to him for?

129
00:06:37,272 --> 00:06:38,815
WOMAN: According to the staff,

130
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:41,776
the victim was stabbed
in the stomach with a knife.

131
00:06:41,776 --> 00:06:44,529
The police are waiting
for Mr. Orihara to recover‐‐

132
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:47,532
‐ So he went and got himself
stabbed, huh?

133
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:49,159
MAN: On to our next story‐‐

134
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,077
‐ I guess he won't be
coming back here for a while,

135
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:53,496
so I'll have the place
all to myself.

136
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,040
MAN:
The city of Higashimurayama‐‐

137
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:57,083
[Namie sighs]

138
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:58,835
‐ Seiji.

139
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:00,920
‐ And in other news today‐‐

140
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:08,219
<i>♪ ♪</i>

141
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,846
Orihara to recover
so they can find out

142
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:11,848
if this was a random attack.

143
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:13,892
‐ On to our next story.

144
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:15,310
Who owns the r‐‐

145
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:18,605
‐ People getting stabbed.
How scary.

146
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:20,649
‐ All right.
You guys ready to head out?

147
00:07:20,649 --> 00:07:22,567
‐ Oh, honey.
Don't be so impatient.

148
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,944
There's still a few hours
before the stores close.

149
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:27,155
‐ I know, I know,
but it's been so long

150
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:29,699
since the three of us
went shopping together.

151
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:31,076
Am I right, Rio?

152
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:32,911
‐ Yeah. I guess it has.

153
00:07:32,911 --> 00:07:35,038
Someone with a normal daily life

154
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:37,666
using their holiday
to go do the unusual

155
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:39,501
is one thing,

156
00:07:39,501 --> 00:07:42,337
but what do people
with unusual daily lives

157
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:44,255
do on their days off?

158
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:48,093
People
who are anything but ordinary.

159
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:52,305
<i>♪ ♪</i>

160
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:56,518
People who are up to their necks
in the unusual.

161
00:07:56,518 --> 00:07:58,228
‐ Hey, Mikado.

162
00:07:58,228 --> 00:07:59,562
Yo, Mikado!

163
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:00,397
‐ Huh?

164
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:02,357
Hey, Seiji.
Mika.

165
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:03,608
How's it going?

166
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:06,277
RIO:
Maybe they don't get holidays.

167
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:12,242
Maybe instead, they look
for other kinds of stimulation.

168
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:14,077
‐ Man, I'm bored.

169
00:08:14,077 --> 00:08:15,995
RIO: One can imagine
he's enjoying

170
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:17,831
how things turned out.

171
00:08:17,831 --> 00:08:21,334
Perhaps he even enjoys
the fact he got stabbed.

172
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,794
But so far,

173
00:08:22,794 --> 00:08:26,840
the day wasn't the usual
normal day he was used to.

174
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:29,801
Normal for him was on hold.

175
00:08:29,801 --> 00:08:33,638
IZAYA: I wonder if the rumors
I planted are sprouting yet.

176
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:36,141
MAN: Yo. I heard
Shizuo got hit by a truck,

177
00:08:36,141 --> 00:08:37,517
and now he's on life support.

178
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:39,060
MAN: The yakuza was chasing him.

179
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,145
He jumped off a building,

180
00:08:40,145 --> 00:08:41,521
and bam‐‐
pancake!

181
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,481
MAN: He's in the hospital,
all effed up.

182
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:45,525
MAN: Dude, you haven't even
heard the best part.

183
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,068
He's got a girlfriend now,

184
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:49,529
and get this‐‐
chick's got a freaking kid!

185
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,990
IZAYA:
And then someone will think...

186
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:54,325
MAN: Now's the time, man.
It's perfect.

187
00:08:54,325 --> 00:08:56,453
You and me‐‐
we can take out Shizuo.

188
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:57,454
‐ Hmm?

189
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:00,040
‐ Bang.

190
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:03,501
[laughing]

191
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:05,503
[grunts]
Ow. Ow.

192
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,714
Heh.
[sighs]

193
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:11,092
Oh, well.
A guy can dream, can't he?

194
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:16,598
[cell phone whistles]

195
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:27,901
<i>♪ ♪</i>

196
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:31,863
RIO:
The city never takes a break,

197
00:09:31,863 --> 00:09:33,531
even on holidays.

198
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:35,366
It keeps moving right along,

199
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:39,037
even after everything
that happened yesterday.

200
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:45,585
<i>♪ ♪</i>

201
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:47,295
‐ Mr. Akabayashi?

202
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:52,092
RIO: It keeps on moving,
feeding off everyone's grief.

203
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:54,052
<i>♪ ♪</i>

204
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:56,721
MASAOMI: I can't help him.

205
00:09:56,721 --> 00:09:59,599
All I can do
is wait for him to get over it

206
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:03,394
and maybe then go talk to him.

207
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:06,815
No! That's not gonna fix
a damn thing!

208
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:10,068
All I want's for him,
Anri, and me to be like we were.

209
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:17,075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

210
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:31,589
IZAYA: Um, nurse?

211
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:32,507
‐ Yes?

212
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:33,508
‐ I hate to bother you,

213
00:10:33,508 --> 00:10:34,843
but may I use your phone?

214
00:10:34,843 --> 00:10:36,678
I'd like to call a friend.

215
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:37,637
‐ Of course.

216
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:39,097
Here. Help yourself.

217
00:10:39,097 --> 00:10:40,223
‐ Hold it!
Don't move!

218
00:10:40,223 --> 00:10:42,767
That's perfect!

219
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:44,477
Okay!

220
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:45,603
No!

221
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:48,356
No‐oh!

222
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,775
‐ Hello?
SHINRA: Who the hell is this?

223
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:52,443
‐ Congratulations.

224
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:55,780
That was the most enthusiastic
greeting I've ever gotten.

225
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,365
‐ Oh, it's you, Izaya.

226
00:10:57,365 --> 00:10:59,659
I'll call you back.
IZAYA: Wait. Don't hang up.

227
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:00,952
I'm in the hospital,

228
00:11:00,952 --> 00:11:02,579
and you're the first person
I called.

229
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:04,622
SHINRA: Wait, what?
Why are you in the hospital?

230
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:07,125
‐ Didn't you see?
It was all over the news today.

231
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:08,960
Got myself stabbed last night.

232
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,378
SHINRA: That sucks.
See you.

233
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:11,671
[line clicks]

234
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:15,466
‐ What a piss‐poor excuse
for a friend.

235
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:21,222
I will have you know,
I'm an upstanding citizen,

236
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:23,308
and it's all your fault
I am here!

237
00:11:23,308 --> 00:11:24,851
You better quit
your life of crime

238
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:26,978
before I end up in the morgue!

239
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,981
All done.
Thank you.

240
00:11:29,981 --> 00:11:31,983
‐ Sure. Don't mention it.

241
00:11:31,983 --> 00:11:33,651
<i>♪ ♪</i>

242
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:36,738
[cell phone trilling]

243
00:11:38,239 --> 00:11:39,991
‐ Hi. Who's this?

244
00:11:39,991 --> 00:11:41,784
Say what?

245
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:43,411
Wait, what?

246
00:11:43,411 --> 00:11:44,787
Yes. That's right.

247
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:48,499
Orihara is my friend.
What about it?

248
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:49,709
Well, actually,

249
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:53,338
I'm sort of out of town
right now, so...

250
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:56,466
Hey, look here!
I am a law‐abiding citizen!

251
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:58,509
[cell phone beeps]

252
00:11:58,509 --> 00:11:59,594
[sighs]

253
00:11:59,594 --> 00:12:02,347
[cell phone trills]

254
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:03,681
IZAYA: It's me again!

255
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:06,893
Hey, did you just get a call
from the cops?

256
00:12:06,893 --> 00:12:08,353
