that you're out there having fun

259
00:12:13,942 --> 00:12:15,276
while I'm stuck in here.

260
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:16,694
I also thought it'd be funny

261
00:12:16,694 --> 00:12:18,112
if I had the cops make a call

262
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:19,572
to the mob's doctor.

263
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:20,782
So, how's it going?

264
00:12:20,782 --> 00:12:21,950
Did this little bit of trauma

265
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:23,826
give you lovers goose pimples?

266
00:12:23,826 --> 00:12:24,827
You can admit it.

267
00:12:24,827 --> 00:12:26,371
I bet it did, right?

268
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:28,831
Hope your hearts don't explode
from the suspense.

269
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:31,417
‐ [laughs]
Yeah. Wouldn't you like to know?

270
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:33,753
I hope the suspense kills you.

271
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:36,297
[tone pulsing]

272
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:47,392
RIO: Her thoughts were racing.

273
00:12:47,392 --> 00:12:49,811
Back then,
she wasn't the only one

274
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:54,816
Nakura tricked into becoming
a potential suicide statistic.

275
00:12:54,816 --> 00:12:58,236
She wondered, were the others
living their lives in this city?

276
00:12:58,236 --> 00:13:01,614
And were they thinking about
the things she was right now?

277
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:10,206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

278
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:12,875
ERIKA: Eh, whatcha gonna do?

