280
00:13:14,711 --> 00:13:16,713
They only compliment
their fave voice actors

281
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:18,131
and dis everyone else's.

282
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:20,633
They're just a bunch
of lowly trolls.

283
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:23,261
Got to shun those dweebs
like pop‐culture lepers.

284
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:25,179
‐ Nicely put,
although what you just said

285
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:27,557
was way harsher
than anything they've said.

286
00:13:27,557 --> 00:13:29,684
‐ So, Fan on top,
Anti on the bottom,

287
00:13:29,684 --> 00:13:31,436
or Anti on top,
Fan on the bottom?

288
00:13:31,436 --> 00:13:34,147
‐ That depends
on if you're talking <i>yuri</i> or BL.

289
00:13:34,147 --> 00:13:35,106
That's like‐‐

290
00:13:35,106 --> 00:13:37,066
‐ Today was kind of chill, huh?

291
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:38,818
‐ You don't sound happy
about it.

292
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:39,777
KYOHEI: Nope.

293
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:40,778
After all the shit

294
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:42,321
that went down yesterday,

295
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:44,615
I thought there'd be
some kind of blowup today too.

296
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:47,118
SABURO: I guess
everyone needs a day off, huh?

297
00:13:47,118 --> 00:13:48,536
‐ Yeah, maybe they do, at that.

298
00:13:48,536 --> 00:13:49,787
Who the hell knows?

299
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:51,622
Man, between the Headless Rider

300
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:53,416
and that demon sword thing,

301
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,793
we saw some crazy stuff
last year.

302
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:57,086
‐ I know.

303
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:59,338
Sure changed
the way I look at the world.

304
00:13:59,338 --> 00:14:00,631
If you told me
there was such a thing

305
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:03,134
as ghosts or aliens,
I'd buy it now.

306
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:05,970
Still, those two things
you mentioned, they're shocking,

307
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:08,681
but front row at Ruri's concert
blew my mind.

308
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,641
‐ That night tops
everything else?

309
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:14,437
Kaztano getting those tickets
was un‐frigging‐believable.

310
00:14:14,437 --> 00:14:16,731
Well,
I guess when you think about it,

311
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:18,107
the world's got its own way

312
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:20,151
of balancing everything out
in the end.

313
00:14:20,151 --> 00:14:23,071
I mean, here we are,
rolling along right now,

314
00:14:23,071 --> 00:14:24,655
taking her easy,

315
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:26,240
but I bet
somewhere else in Japan,

316
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,534
something crazy's going down

317
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:29,494
for someone else.

318
00:14:29,494 --> 00:14:31,162
‐ Getting philosophical now?

319
00:14:31,162 --> 00:14:33,581
KYOHEI: Hey, we're in deep
with stuff like the Black Bike

320
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:35,458
