it's one hell of a mess, though,

329
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:57,688
thanks to you Nebula clowns.

330
00:14:57,688 --> 00:14:59,190
SHINGEN: Well, today,
I'm not here

331
00:14:59,190 --> 00:15:00,650
as an employee of Nebula.

332
00:15:00,650 --> 00:15:03,319
I'm here as an old friend
giving you fair warning.

333
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:04,403
SEITARO: About what?

334
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:07,198
‐ Jinnai Yodogiri.
‐ [gasps]

335
00:15:07,198 --> 00:15:10,034
SHINGEN: Judging by
that choky sound you made,

336
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:11,702
the rumors are true.

337
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:15,039
If I were you, I'd stay as
far away from him as possible.

338
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,458
‐ You saying
he's some kind of threat?

339
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,001
He's just an old info broker

340
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:22,213
who likes groveling in the dirt
before his superiors.

341
00:15:22,213 --> 00:15:25,216
‐ The threat Yodogiri poses
is like a poison,

342
00:15:25,216 --> 00:15:27,426
like radiation‐‐
it'll eat away at you

343
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:29,470
and contaminate
everything you love.

344
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:32,640
Slow. Real, real slow.

345
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,684
And by the time you notice
something's wrong,

346
00:15:34,684 --> 00:15:37,228
it's already too late.

347
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:38,938
You think you can use him
for all he's worth

348
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:41,482
and then toss him away
if things get dicey,

349
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:44,610
but that's just
your arrogance talking.

350
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:47,697
<i>[ethereal choral music]</i>

351
00:15:47,697 --> 00:15:49,073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

352
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:50,825
I know
your nephew's infatuated

353
00:15:50,825 --> 00:15:51,826
with that head.

354
00:15:51,826 --> 00:15:54,078
Could it be you are too?

355
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:56,789
‐ Heh. You don't know
what you're talking about.

356
00:15:56,789 --> 00:16:00,751
‐ I'm talking about you being
obsessed by something inhuman.

357
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,920
‐ Huh. As I said before,

358
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:05,423
you don't know
what you're talking about.

359
00:16:05,423 --> 00:16:08,843
Appreciate the warning, though.

360
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:10,803
[car door thuds]

361
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:13,598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

362
00:16:13,598 --> 00:16:15,474
EGOR: This man called Yodogiri.

363
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:17,768
Is he as dangerous as you say?

364
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:19,187
SHINGEN: Why, Egor?

365
00:16:19,187 --> 00:16:20,354
Does that worry you?

366
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:21,272
‐ No.

367
00:16:21,272 --> 00:16:22,940
‐ Do you remember Hollywood?

368
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,233
The serial killer?

369
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,943
EGOR: The plastic surgery
I went through

370
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:28,529
guarantees I'll never forget.

371
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,239
‐ But ask yourself
why Hollywood,

372
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:32,909
or rather Ms. Hijiribe,
didn't kill him outright.

373
00:16:32,909 --> 00:16:36,662
She had every opportunity,
but the fact is, she didn't.

374
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:40,625
That should tell you
just how abnormal he really is.

375
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:41,918
EGOR: I see your point,

376
00:16:41,918 --> 00:16:43,336
but then
why would a man like that

377
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:44,587
partner up with the CEO

378
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:47,089
of Yagiri Pharmaceuticals?

379
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:48,799
‐ The answer lies in the facts.

380
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:50,343
His talent agency was a front,

381
00:16:50,343 --> 00:16:52,136
and he <i>is</i> a broker.

382
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,846
‐ What are you saying?

383
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:56,057
Is he a human trafficker
or something?

384
00:16:56,057 --> 00:16:58,726
‐ Yodogiri sells humans
and other things.

385
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:00,186
EGOR: Like what?

386
00:17:00,186 --> 00:17:01,812
SHINGEN: Oh...
like where to find

387
00:17:01,812 --> 00:17:03,147
the demon sword Saika

388
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:04,607
and the lair of the Dullahan.

389
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:07,818
I bought that information
from him 20 years ago.

390
00:17:07,818 --> 00:17:09,320
<i>[moody bell music]</i>

391
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:10,613
By the way, Egor,

392
00:17:10,613 --> 00:17:12,823
something's been bothering me
lately.

393
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:15,284
‐ Really? What?

394
00:17:15,284 --> 00:17:17,912
‐ Did Saika cut you
the other day?

395
00:17:17,912 --> 00:17:21,374
‐ That's for me to know
and you to find out.

396
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:34,095
[footsteps clomping
synchronously]

397
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:40,851
IZAYA: Come in, whoever you are.

398
00:17:40,851 --> 00:17:44,605
RIO: And so, at the end
of an unusually boring day,

399
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:48,776
he was about to experience
another unexpected thing.

400
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:50,861
[footsteps shuffling]

401
00:17:57,994 --> 00:17:59,370
‐ Uh...

402
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:00,955
‐ At last.

403
00:18:00,955 --> 00:18:02,790
I found you.

404
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,125
<i>[uncertain string music]</i>

405
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:05,334
‐ You have?

406
00:18:05,334 --> 00:18:07,253
I'm sorry.

407
00:18:07,253 --> 00:18:08,254
Who are you?

408
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:09,880
‐ What, you don't remember?

409
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,215
I guess you wouldn't.

410
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:13,551
No, I bet
I'm probably the biggest nobody

411
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:15,386
a person like you has ever met.

412
00:18:15,386 --> 00:18:17,054
‐ [laughs]
You must be right.

413
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:19,056
Otherwise, I'd remember you.

414
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:21,684
‐ "When you die, you disappear.

415
00:18:21,684 --> 00:18:23,978
"The pain you feel doesn't,
though.

416
00:18:23,978 --> 00:18:25,479
Only your being."

417
00:18:25,479 --> 00:18:28,774
IZAYA: Wait.
That sounds familiar.

418
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:30,109
‐ "You say there's nothing,

419
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:32,445
"but eternal darkness
isn't nothing.

420
00:18:32,445 --> 00:18:36,574
It's definitely there,
and you feel it all around you."

421
00:18:36,574 --> 00:18:37,908
‐ Ah.

422
00:18:40,828 --> 00:18:44,457
So, ladies, what do you think
happens after you die?

423
00:18:45,416 --> 00:18:46,542
‐ What do you mean?

424
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:47,960
You asking
if we believe in Heaven?

425
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,463
‐ I don't believe
in a Heaven or a hell.

426
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:52,006
When you die, there's nothing.

427
00:18:52,006 --> 00:18:53,424
It's dark.
That's it.

428
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:55,676
But at least
it's better than here.

429
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:56,844
‐ Oh, please.

430
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:58,429
Why do suicidal people
always think

431
00:18:58,429 --> 00:18:59,930
the afterlife is better?

432
00:18:59,930 --> 00:19:01,182
I hate to say this,

433
00:19:01,182 --> 00:19:03,142
but it's obvious
neither of you have given

434
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:05,061
any serious thought
to the matter.

435
00:19:05,061 --> 00:19:07,271
You're just making
blind assumptions.

436
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:09,899
But if you think eternity's
better, kill yourself.

437
00:19:09,899 --> 00:19:12,902
There's too many people
on this planet anyway.

438
00:19:12,902 --> 00:19:16,947
‐ Um, Nakura, you don't sound
like you want to commit suicide.

439
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:19,909
‐ Oh, God, no.

440
00:19:19,909 --> 00:19:21,494
‐ You were lying to us
this whole time?

441
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:23,329
‐ You jerk.
That's beyond cruel!

442
00:19:23,329 --> 00:19:25,456
‐ Who cares?
BOTH: Huh?

443
00:19:25,456 --> 00:19:27,416
‐ You guys made up your minds
to die already,

444
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,126
so why do you care anymore?

445
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:31,462
It's not like you'll be around
much longer,

446
00:19:31,462 --> 00:19:34,215
so what does it matter
if I tricked you?

447
00:19:35,383 --> 00:19:36,425
‐ Our drinks.

448
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:38,344
[clothes ruffle]
[Manami gasps]

449
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,013
IZAYA: You said after you died,

450
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,473
there'd be nothing,

451
00:19:42,473 --> 00:19:43,933
but what I think you meant

452
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:46,268
was that you wouldn't
have to suffer anymore.

453
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:48,479
See, when you die,
you disappear.

454
00:19:48,479 --> 00:19:51,065
The pain you feel doesn't,
though.

455
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:52,775
Only your being.

456
00:19:52,775 --> 00:19:54,068
You say there's nothing,

457
00:19:54,068 --> 00:19:56,153
but eternal darkness
isn't nothing.

458
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:59,615
It's definitely there,
and you feel it all around you.

459
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:02,034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

460
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,829
You know, I can't sense
any love in your deaths.

461
00:20:04,829 --> 00:20:07,248
That's bad.
You have to love death.

462
00:20:07,248 --> 00:20:09,458
You have to respect
the darkness.

463
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:13,045
I can't kill myself with you
if you're not serious about it.

464
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:15,840
‐ I'll make you pay.

465
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:17,466
I'll kill you.

466
00:20:17,466 --> 00:20:20,136
I swear.

467
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:21,512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

468
00:20:21,512 --> 00:20:25,558
‐ Well, looks like another job
for the transporter.

469
00:20:25,558 --> 00:20:28,185
Oh. It's her.

470
00:20:28,185 --> 00:20:30,354
‐ Get ready,
'cause this nobody's come back

471
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:32,148
to cut the life out of you!

472
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:37,319
‐ You're right.

473
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,029
You don't mean anything to me.

474
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:42,199
You didn't even have the guts
to commit suicide,

475
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:43,659
but you spent the past year

476
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:45,953
waiting
for the chance to kill me,

477
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,913
and then, today,
you saw the news,

478
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:50,249
and then, somehow,
you found me.

479
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:52,501
And now here you are!

480
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:53,836
You've come to kill me!

481
00:20:53,836 --> 00:20:56,046
Isn't it amazing
how things work out?

482
00:20:56,046 --> 00:20:58,382
This was the last thing
I ever expected.

483
00:20:58,382 --> 00:21:01,552
Oh, I remember now,
and it's all thanks to you.

484
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:06,348
I remember everything‐‐
how I started, what drives me.

485
00:21:06,348 --> 00:21:08,517
Ever since
I found something inhuman,

486
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:10,811
I've been selling humanity
short,

487
00:21:10,811 --> 00:21:12,772
but not anymore!

488
00:21:12,772 --> 00:21:14,190
Humans are magnificent!

489
00:21:14,190 --> 00:21:16,484
I can't believe
I ever doubted it.

490
00:21:16,484 --> 00:21:18,819
Magnificent! Magnificent!
[laughs]

491
00:21:18,819 --> 00:21:21,572
‐ I don't get whatever it is
you're flipping out about.

492
00:21:21,572 --> 00:21:24,074
All I know is,
you're lower than dirt.

493
00:21:24,074 --> 00:21:25,284
‐ Fine by me!

494
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:27,453
Go ahead
and hate me all you want.

495
00:21:27,453 --> 00:21:28,913
I'll keep on loving you.

496
00:21:28,913 --> 00:21:31,373
Obsessively.
Irrationally!

497
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:33,793
Desperately!
I love humanity!

498
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:35,503
I love every one of you!

499
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:39,340
[clock ticking]

500
00:21:47,765 --> 00:21:50,142
CELTY: All I can say is, wow!

501
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:52,102
SHINRA: Now you see
what I was talking about?

502
00:21:52,102 --> 00:21:55,105
‐ You know that wolf we saw?
The one you said was extinct?

503
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:58,150
I still can't believe
it turned out to be a werewolf.

504
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:01,111
And what was up with those
priestesses at that shrine?

505
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:04,365
They were so giving off
this vampire vibe.

506
00:22:04,365 --> 00:22:05,616
[elevator dings]

507
00:22:05,616 --> 00:22:07,743
Well,
I think I'll go take a shower.

508
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:10,788
‐ Can we take one together
for once?

509
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:13,707
‐ It's about time.

